{"questionId":"21513","questionHtml":"<p>A person with a weight of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>600</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>N</mtext></math> stands on a scale in an elevator.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/ebc60f507a106354b940561ad8a214efd4bc40ca.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the acceleration of the elevator when the scale reads <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>900</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>N</mtext></math>?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>m s</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> downwards</p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>m s</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> downwards</p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>m s</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> upwards</p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>m s</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> upwards</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"21513","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ2.5","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A person with a weight of 600 N stands on a scale in an elevator. What is the acceleration of the elevator when the scale reads 900 N? A. 5.0 m s-2 downwards B. 1.5 m s-2 downwards","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"5","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.2 – Forces","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}